<p><strong>Content-Type support:</strong> <code>application/x-www-form-urlencoded</code>,
<code>multipart/form-data</code> (required for <code>file</code> uploads), and
<code>application/json</code> (all fields except <code>file</code>).</p>
<p>{{call .Translate `docsAPIv1.ResponseExample`}}</p>
{{ call .Highlight `{
	"id": "XcmX9ON1",
	"url": "https://paste.example.com/XcmX9ON1",
	"createTime": 1653387358,
	"deleteTime": 0
}` `json`}}

<details>
	<summary><strong>Code Examples</strong></summary>

	<h5>cURL — form data</h5>
	{{ call .Highlight (printf `curl -sS -X POST %s/api/v1/pastes \
  -H "Accept: application/json" \
  -F "title=My Paste" \
  -F "body=Hello World" \
  -F "syntax=autodetect" \
  -F "expiration=3600" \
  | jq -r '.data.url'` .ServerURL) "bash" }}

	<h5>cURL — JSON body</h5>
	{{ call .Highlight (printf `curl -sS -X POST %s/api/v1/pastes \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Accept: application/json" \
  -d '{"title":"My Paste","body":"Hello World","syntax":"autodetect","expiration":3600}' \
  | jq -r '.data.url'` .ServerURL) "bash" }}

	<h5>cURL — file upload</h5>
	{{ call .Highlight (printf `curl -sS -X POST %s/api/v1/pastes \
  -F "file=@screenshot.png" \
  | jq -r '.data.url'` .ServerURL) "bash" }}

	<h5>Node.js</h5>
	{{ call .Highlight (printf `const response = await fetch('%s/api/v1/pastes', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: {
    'Content-Type': 'application/json',
    'Accept': 'application/json',
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    title: 'My Paste',
    body: 'Hello World',
    syntax: 'autodetect',
    expiration: 3600,
  }),
});
const { data } = await response.json();
console.log('Paste URL:', data.url);` .ServerURL) "javascript" }}

	<h5>Python</h5>
	{{ call .Highlight (printf `import requests

r = requests.post('%s/api/v1/pastes', json={
    'title': 'My Paste',
    'body': 'Hello World',
    'syntax': 'autodetect',
    'expiration': 3600,
})
print('Paste URL:', r.json()['data']['url'])` .ServerURL) "python" }}
</details>


<h4 id="get">GET <code>/api/v1/pastes/{id}</code></h4>
<p>Get a single paste by ID. Two equivalent forms are accepted:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Query parameter: <code>GET /api/v1/pastes?id={id}</code></li>
	<li>Path segment: <code>GET /api/v1/pastes/{id}</code></li>
</ul>
<p>{{call .Translate `docsAPIv1.RequestParameters`}}</p>
<table>
	<th>{{call .Translate `docsAPIv1.Field`}}</th>
	<th>{{call .Translate `docsAPIv1.Required`}}</th>
	<th>{{call .Translate `docsAPIv1.Default`}}</th>
	<th>{{call .Translate `docsAPIv1.Description`}}</th>
	<tr>
		<td><code>id</code></td>
		<td>{{call .Translate `docsAPIv1.RequiredYes`}}</td>
		<td></td>
		<td>{{call .Translate `docsAPIv1.ReqGetID`}}</td>
	</tr>
</table>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> Burn-after-reading pastes (<code>oneUse: true</code>) are automatically deleted after retrieval. The full content is returned and the paste is immediately removed.</p>
<p>{{call .Translate `docsAPIv1.ResponseExample`}}</p>
{{ call .Highlight `{
	"id": "XcmX9ON1",
	"title": "Paste title.",
	"body": "Line 1.\nLine 2.\nLine 3.\n\nLine 5.",
	"createTime": 1653387358,
	"deleteTime": 0,
	"oneUse": false,
	"syntax": "plaintext",
	"author": "Anon",
	"authorEmail": "me@example.org",
	"authorURL": "https://example.org"
}` `json`}}

<details>
	<summary><strong>Code Examples</strong></summary>

	<h5>cURL — query param</h5>
	{{ call .Highlight (printf "curl -sS %s/api/v1/pastes?id=XcmX9ON1 | jq -r '.data.body'" .ServerURL) "bash" }}

	<h5>cURL — path style (equivalent)</h5>
	{{ call .Highlight (printf "curl -sS %s/api/v1/pastes/XcmX9ON1 | jq -r '.data.body'" .ServerURL) "bash" }}

	<h5>Node.js</h5>
	{{ call .Highlight (printf `const response = await fetch('%s/api/v1/pastes/XcmX9ON1');
const { data } = await response.json();
console.log('Body:', data.body);` .ServerURL) "javascript" }}

	<h5>Python</h5>
	{{ call .Highlight (printf `import requests

r = requests.get('%s/api/v1/pastes/XcmX9ON1')
print('Body:', r.json()['data']['body'])` .ServerURL) "python" }}
</details>


<h4 id="list">GET <code>/api/v1/pastes</code></h4>
<p>List recent pastes. Returns an array of paste objects.</p>
<p>{{call .Translate `docsAPIv1.RequestParameters`}}</p>
<table>
	<th>{{call .Translate `docsAPIv1.Field`}}</th>
	<th>{{call .Translate `docsAPIv1.Required`}}</th>
	<th>{{call .Translate `docsAPIv1.Default`}}</th>
	<th>{{call .Translate `docsAPIv1.Description`}}</th>
	<tr>
		<td><code>limit</code></td>
		<td></td>
		<td><code>50</code></td>
		<td>Maximum number of pastes to return (1-100)</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td><code>offset</code></td>
		<td></td>
		<td><code>0</code></td>
		<td>Number of pastes to skip (for pagination)</td>
	</tr>
</table>
<p>{{call .Translate `docsAPIv1.ResponseExample`}}</p>
{{ call .Highlight `[
	{
		"id": "XcmX9ON1",
		"title": "Paste title.",
		"createTime": 1653387358,
		"deleteTime": 0,
		"syntax": "plaintext"
	},
	{
		"id": "AbC12345",
		"title": "Another paste",
		"createTime": 1653387100,
		"deleteTime": 1653473500,
		"syntax": "go"
	}
]` `json`}}

<details>
	<summary><strong>Code Examples</strong></summary>

	<h5>cURL</h5>
	{{ call .Highlight (printf "curl -sS %s/api/v1/pastes | jq '.[].id'" .ServerURL) "bash" }}
	{{ call .Highlight (printf "curl -sS \"%s/api/v1/pastes?limit=10&offset=20\" | jq '.[].id'" .ServerURL) "bash" }}

	<h5>Node.js</h5>
	{{ call .Highlight (printf `const response = await fetch('%s/api/v1/pastes');
const pastes = await response.json();
pastes.forEach(p => console.log(p.id, p.title));` .ServerURL) "javascript" }}

	<h5>Python</h5>
	{{ call .Highlight (printf `import requests

pastes = requests.get('%s/api/v1/pastes').json()
for p in pastes:
    print(p['id'], p['title'])` .ServerURL) "python" }}
</details>


